Data Structures Information

Data Structure Operation Description Time Complexity Space Complexity
BST Insertion Inserts a new node into the Binary Search Tree. O(log n) O(n)
Deletion Deletes a node from the Binary Search Tree. Deletes a specified node from the tree while maintaining the binary search tree property. O(log n) O(n)
Search Searches for a node with a given key in the Binary Search Tree. Traverses the tree from the root node comparing keys until a match is found or the tree is exhausted. O(log n) O(1) - for balanced BST, O(n) - for skewed BST
Traversal Traverses the Binary Search Tree in different orders (in-order, pre-order, post-order). Visits each node of the tree exactly once, displaying or processing node data in some manner. O(n) O(n)
AVL Insertion Inserts a new node into the AVL tree and performs rotations to maintain balance. O(log n) O(n)
Deletion Deletes a node from the AVL tree and performs rotations to maintain balance. Deletes a specified node from the tree while maintaining the AVL balance property. O(log n) O(n)
Search Searches for a node with a given key in the AVL tree. Traverses the tree from the root node comparing keys until a match is found or the tree is exhausted. O(log n) O(1)
Traversal Traverses the AVL tree in different orders (in-order, pre-order, post-order). Visits each node of the tree exactly once, displaying or processing node data in some manner. O(n) O(n)
Trie Insertion Inserts a new key into the trie. O(m), m = length of key O(n * m), n = number of keys
Deletion Deletes a key from the trie. Deletes a specified key from the trie. O(m) O(1)
Search Searches for a key in the trie. Searches for a specified key in the trie. O(m) O(1)
Prefix Search Finds all keys with the given prefix. Searches for all keys in the trie with a specified prefix. O(m), m = length of prefix O(1)
Heap (Max/Min) Insertion Inserts a new element into the heap. O(log n) O(n)
Deletion Deletes the root element from the heap. Deletes the root element from the heap and restores heap properties. O(log n) O(1)
Extract Max/Min Extracts the maximum/minimum element from the heap. Extracts and removes the maximum/minimum element from the heap and restores heap properties. O(log n) O(1)
Heapify Builds a heap from an array of elements. Builds a heap data structure from an array of elements in linear time. O(n) O(1)
